<subSubSection id="C363AAB6FF83C515FF12F9FBFF4EFEE6" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BC6F93DFF83C515FF12F9FBFF4EFEE6" blockId="15.[151,1436,1919,2020]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,152,476]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF83C50AFF12F9FBFEAFF87B" bold="true" box="[196,263,1957,1983]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF83C50AFF12F9FBFF57F87B" box="[196,255,1957,1983]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Reitter’s collection at 
<collectionCode id="ED6861F8FF83C50AFDEFF9FBFD3EF87B" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[569,662,1957,1983]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">HNHM</collectionCode>
, is a female (pinned through the right elytron which was cracked toward base of elytral humeri, elytra separated) bearing the handwritten labels: “Akbes”, “ 
<collectingCountry id="F36EB9ADFF83C50AFB31F994FA84F820" box="[1255,1324,1994,2020]" name="Syria" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Syria</collectingCountry>
, Akbes”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FF72FEC6FE20FF75" box="[164,392,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexicollis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FF72FEC6FE20FF75" box="[164,392,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus convexicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23E9854FF9CC515FE46FEC6FE79FF76" box="[400,465,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Petri”, “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FDEFFEC6FD13FF76" box="[569,699,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Holotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FD11FEC6FCADFF76" box="[711,773,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FCC4FEC6FB92FF76" authority="Petri" authorityName="Petri" box="[786,1082,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexicollis">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FCC4FEC6FC5EFF75" box="[786,1014,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus convexicollis</emphasis>
Petri
</taxonomicName>
” red brimmed museum label, and fitting the description with 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FDDDFEE3FD96FF13" box="[523,574,189,215]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality as Akbes, Caucasus, Araxes, and is here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FAE6FEE3FA33FF13" box="[1328,1435,189,215]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">lectotype</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FF08FEBCFECFFF38" box="[222,359,226,252]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, Ƥ, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FE4CFEBCFC94FF38" authority="Petri., Gultekin" authorityName="Petri., Gultekin" box="[410,828,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexicollis">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FE4CFEBCFDD5FF3F" box="[410,637,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus convexicollis</emphasis>
Petri., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FCACFEBCFC12FF38" box="[890,954,226,252]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FC09FEBCFAC1FF38" authority="Boh., Gultekin" authorityName="Boh., Gultekin" box="[991,1385,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FC09FEBCFB19FF3F" box="[991,1201,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus elegantulus</emphasis>
Boh., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
det. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FF41FF56FF70FEE6" box="[151,216,264,290]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363AAB6FF9CC515FF12FF73FD89FE18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC6F93DFF9CC515FF12FF73FD89FE18" blockId="16.[151,1437,152,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FF12FF73FE96FE83" bold="true" box="[196,318,301,327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the only specimen in Reitter’s collection fitting the original description of the species. 
<collectingCountry id="F36EB9ADFF9CC515FF41FF0CFF10FEA8" box="[151,184,338,364]" name="American Samoa" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">As</collectingCountry>
seen below under 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FE42FF0CFDEAFEAF" box="[404,578,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FE42FF0CFDEAFEAF" box="[404,578,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. amplirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this is the opposite sex of the 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FC79FF0CFC49FEA8" box="[943,993,338,364]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FBDFFF0CFB1EFEAF" box="[1033,1206,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FBDFFF0CFB1EFEAF" box="[1033,1206,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. amplirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a female. They share the same locality of “Akbes” in 
<collectingCountry id="F36EB9ADFF9CC515FD4DFF26FD59FE56" box="[667,753,376,402]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF9CC515FD2AFF26FC3EFE56" author="Petri" box="[764,918,376,402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="21" refString="Petri, K. (1904 a) Beschreibung einiger neuer Lixus - arten. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 23 (3 - 4): 65 - 77." type="journal article" year="1904" yearSuffix="a">
Petri (
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FC92FF26FC29FE56" box="[836,897,376,402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
described the gender difference as different species. Designation of a new synonymy is necessary: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FCBCFFC3FA8EFE73" authority="Boheman, 1842" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1842" box="[874,1318,413,439]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FCBCFFC3FBF8FE72" box="[874,1104,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus elegantulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF9CC515FB8CFFC3FA8EFE73" author="Boheman" box="[1114,1318,413,439]" pageId="16" pageNumber="20" refString="Boheman, C. H. (1842) In Schoenherr C. J. [1842]. Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Species novae aut hactenus minus cognitae, descriptionibus a Dom. L. Gyllenhal, C. H. Boheman, O. J. Fahraeus, et entomologis aliis illustratae. Tomus septimus. Pars prima. Supplementum continens. Roret, Paris; Fleischer, Lipsiae, [II] + 1 - 479 pp." type="journal article" year="1842">
Boheman, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FB30FFC3FA8EFE73" box="[1254,1318,413,439]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1842.0">1842</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FA81FFC3FE10FE18" authority="Petri, 1904" authorityName="Petri" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexicollis" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FA81FFC3FE98FE1F" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus convexicollis</emphasis>
Petri, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FEABFF9CFE10FE18" box="[381,440,450,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FE69FF9CFDB8FE18" bold="true" box="[447,528,450,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23E9854FF9CC515FE69FF9CFDB8FE18" box="[447,528,450,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
